  "texts": [
    "10 The benefits and challenges of IoT in agriculture 10.1 Benefits of IoT in agriculture",
    "The Internet of Things (IoT) plays a crucial role in optimizing water management, reducing labor efforts, and improving crop yield through efficient monitoring and automation (Badoni et al. 2023).",
    "By integrating IoT sensors and devices, farmers can collect real-time data on environmental conditions, soil moisture levels, and crop health that helps them make informed decisions on irrigation, fertilization, and pest control, maximizing resource utilization and crop productivity (Jadhav et al. 2024).",
    "IoT-based precision agriculture systems can increase crop yields by up to 20% compared to traditional methods (Digra et al. 2025).",
    "Integrating Green-IoT and AI/ML technologies facilitates automated irrigation and livestock monitoring, which can lead to even greater yields (Shrivastav et al. 2024)."
  ],
